<TITLE> Mob kills 3 robbers in Brahmanbaria </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, Jan 15 (bdnews24.com)--Three robbers were killed by a mob at Bitghor in Nabinagar Upazila of Brahmanbaria early on Friday, said police and locals. 'Tiger' Samad, alleged leader of the robbers in the district, was among the dead, Brahmanbari additional police superintendent Osman Gani told reporters. There were 15 cases against him, said Goni. The other killed are 'Mofiz', 38, and 'Ilyas', 39. Police arrested a 25-year old Beauty Begum, who they said was a member of the gang. The villagers surrounded 20-25 robbers at around 3 am and nabbed four of them, Shongram Mia of Bitghor area told bdnews24.com. The mob had beaten up and killed three on the spot before police reached there, said officer in charge of Nabinagar Police Station Rupok Kumar Saha. "Only Beauty was rescued from the mob," he said. A local-made firearm and nine rounds of bullet were recovered from the spot. The bodies were sent to the Sadar Hospital for autopsy. bd
